\f0\fs24 \cf0 Mini-DSSP (Karim Bouchaara \'97 M2 Bioinformatics, Universit\'e9 Paris Cit\'e9)\
\
A compact, transparent re-implementation of DSSP core rules for protein secondary-structure assignment. It follows Kabsch & Sander (1983): electrostatic CO\'b7\'b7\'b7NH hydrogen-bond energy plus motif rules (n-turns for helices; beta-bridges chained into ladders for sheets), with a DSSP-like priority to merge states.\
\
States produced: G/H/I, E/B, T (others default to C).\
Evaluation reported in H/E/C (mapping G,I->H and B->E) as Q3.\
\
