Usage\
\
3.1 Run mini-DSSP on a PDB\
\
Example: chain A of 1CRN\
python dssp_bouchaara.py data/1CRN.pdb --chain A > /tmp/1CRN.out\
Extract the per-residue summary line into preds/:\
grep -A2 "Summary (per residue)" /tmp/1CRN.out | tail -n1 > preds/1CRN.pred.ss\
\
Parameters:\
--chain A (default A)\
--cutoff -0.45 (kcal/mol; try -0.40 or -0.55 for sensitivity)\
-v (verbose counts)\
--print-bridges\
--print-hb\
\
3.2 Build DSSP references with mkdssp\
\
Compute DSSP (DSSP format autodetected from the output extension):\
pixi run -- mkdssp data/1CRN.pdb refs/1CRN.dssp\
\
Extract the summary SS string (spaces -> C):\
python - <<'PY' > refs/1CRN.ref.ss\
ss=[]; go=False\
for line in open("refs/1CRN.dssp"):\
if line.startswith(" # RESIDUE"): go=True; continue\
if not go or not line.strip(): continue\
c = line[16] if len(line)>16 else ' '\
ss.append(c if c!=' ' else 'C')\
print("".join(ss))\
PY\
\
Method (what the script does)\
\
Parse PDB (Bio.PDB). Keep backbone N, CA, C, O and ignore HETATM and waters; require all four atoms.\
\
Place virtual H on N if missing: bisector of N\'96C and N\'96CA (or prev C and N\'96CA when peptide link is intact), with |N\'96H| approx 1.0 \'c5.\
\
Compute DSSP-style H-bond energy:\
E = 332 * q1 * q2 * (1/r_ON + 1/r_CH - 1/r_OH - 1/r_CN), with q1=0.42, q2=0.20.\
Accept CO(i)->NH(j) if E < cutoff (default -0.45 kcal/mol).\
\
Detect n-turns (i->i+3/4/5). Two consecutive n-turns seed G/H/I; extend by overlap.\
\
Detect beta-bridges (parallel/antiparallel patterns), chain them into ladders.\
Residues in ladders with >=2 bridges -> E; single bridge -> B.\
\
Add non-helical T at turn endpoints still in coil; merge conflicts by priority:\
H > B > E > G > I > T > C to produce one letter per residue.\
\
Evaluation protocol (H/E/C and Q3)\
\
Map fine states to three classes: G,I->H ; B->E ; others unchanged (H,E; else C).\
Q3 = fraction of residues where Pred == Ref in H/E/C.\
Confusion matrices (rows = Ref, cols = Pred) are provided in results/.\
\
